{"article_id":"pbUV9hG3e2mBYjRK","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" We have the votes","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"once the impeachment trial has begun","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to pass a resolution essentially the same","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"- very similar -","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"to the 100 to nothing vote in the Clinton trial , \"","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"McConnell told reporters .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"\" All","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"we ' re doing here","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"is saying","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"we ' re going to get started in exactly the same way","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that 100 senators agreed to 20 years ago . \"","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"The GOP leader added","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that the Senate will `` get around to the discussion of witnesses , ''","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"but not before the Senate trial begins .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Schumer reiterated his pledge","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"to force votes on witnesses and documents","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"and offered his own warning to Senate Republicans Tuesday afternoon :","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"`` You can run","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"but you ca n't hide . ''","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"`` Large numbers of Republicans have refused to say","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"whether they are for witnesses and documents","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and that ' s why Leader McConnell came up with this kick-the-can down the road theory , ''","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Schumer said .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"`` McConnell will never go for it","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"but will four of his Republican colleagues ? ''","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"The move is the latest exercise of blunt political power by McConnell ,","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"who since becoming majority leader","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"has found myriad ways","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"to sideline Democrats","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"and move his agenda with narrow majorities .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"And the partisan impeachment road isn ' t without risk :","depth":4},{"id":31,"text":"Republicans are doing little to distance themselves from the president even on process questions , let alone the ultimate decision","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"of whether to remove Trump from office .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Yet Republicans say","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Democrats offered them little alternative :","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Most scoffed at the idea","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"that Schumer could determine what evidence is heard in the Senate .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"And McConnell 's strategy has key backing from the handful of Republican swing votes","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"heading into the trial ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"though many senators , like Lisa Murkowski of Alaska , had hoped","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Schumer and McConnell could come to an agreement .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"\" We ' ve gotten so snarled up with debate over witnesses","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"that the two leaders haven ' t been able to come to terms on this first phase","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"so it looks like we ' ll go forward with a Republican [ package ] , \"","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"said Murkowski ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"who said","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"she would support McConnell ' s proposal .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"\" I ' d like to hear from John Bolton and other witnesses","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to provide information .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"That process will accommodate that .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"The Clinton process allows for a vote on witnesses to occur","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"after opening arguments , ''","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"said Utah Sen. Mitt Romney .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"Speaker Nancy Pelosi has withheld the articles of impeachment","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"since the House voted in December to charge Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress ,","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"in part to push Republicans to agree to fair rules for the trial .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"The GOP used the delay from the House","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"to get ready to start the clock on the impeachment trial as soon as possible .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"`` What we ' re aspiring to do is to get this process moving forward","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"and indicate to the Democrats","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"as soon as they send those articles over here ,","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"we ' re ready to go .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"Quit stalling , ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"said Senate Majority Whip John Thune","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"( R-S.D . ) .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Following McConnell ' s announcement ,","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"the Senate is in a position","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"to quickly begin the trial","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"- even if it requires steamrolling the 47-member minority .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Democrats immediately criticized McConnell","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"for moving forward without them","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"and without making any promise","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"to hear from witnesses .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"`` That ' s not how you run a country .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"That ' s not how you run the United States Senate , ''","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"said Sen. Jon Tester","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"( D-Mont . ) .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"`` That 's regrettable .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"If I thought","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"McConnell 's offer","depth":16},{"id":81,"text":"to bring witnesses ...","depth":16},{"id":82,"text":"was in good faith ,","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"I could probably vote to proceed with impeachment inquiry .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"I do n't believe that , ''","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"said Sen. Chris Murphy","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"( D-Conn. ) .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"he 's going to bring witnesses .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"this is all a whitewash . ''","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"McConnell and Schumer have been unable to reach a deal","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"on how to run the impeachment trial .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"And their efforts at negotiations were anemic ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"boiling down to a 20-minute conversation on December","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that got them no closer to a bipartisan result .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"That impasse squashes hopes","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"of repeating the 100-0 vote","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"that kicked off Clinton ' s trial .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Those circumstances were in some ways different :","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"The Senate had much more information about Clinton 's impeachment inquiry","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"than it has on Trump","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"given this administration 's all-out effort","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"to block witness testimony and documents from the House .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"But McConnell needs only a bare majority","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"to ignore Democrats ' demands","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"to subpoena witnesses and documents","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"and instead kick that decision until later in the trial .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"Schumer has sought to put pressure on McConnell ' s vulnerable senators","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"by raising the question of witnesses","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"and pointing to new emails","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"that have been released","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"showing the president 's involvement in the Ukraine scandal .","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"Trump ' s former national security adviser John Bolton said Monday","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"he would testify before the Senate","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"if subpoenaed .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"But moderate Republicans like Murkowski and Susan Collins of Maine said","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"they are comfortable with following the Clinton model","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"and deciding whether to call witnesses later .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"Schumer and Democrats will still have opportunities","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"to try to shape the trial .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"They can force votes on their preferred trial structure ,","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"which","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"they believe","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"will put vulnerable Republicans in a bind .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"And they could in theory succeed","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"if more senators like Romney decide","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"they need to hear new evidence .","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"`` I know","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"that I 'll want to hear from witnesses , ''","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"Romney said .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"Pelosi could deliver the articles of impeachment as soon as this week .","depth":3},{"id":132,"text":"While she did not secure any concessions from McConnell","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"- who said","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"Democrats were grasping onto `` mythical leverage '' -","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"the party did briefly win new scrutiny on GOP vows","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"to coordinate closely with the White House .","depth":5},{"id":137,"text":"Now after the long holiday break and still no additional response from Pelosi , Republicans are eager to get moving .","depth":4},{"id":138,"text":"The House \" wasn ' t pushing for the witnesses","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"like they should .","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"So why the heck did they expect","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"we ' re going to jump all over it now ? \"","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"said Sen. Joni Ernst","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"( R-Iowa ) ,","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"who is up for reelection .","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"Pelosi is playing a political game right now","depth":4},{"id":146,"text":"and she ' s losing . \"","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":293,"left":277,"right":292,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":176,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":160,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":152,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":148,"right":150,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":154,"right":155,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":153,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":11,"right":157,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":170,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":164,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":161,"right":163,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":161,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":16,"right":162,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":162,"left":17,"right":18,"rel